---
// One idea: some rebuildings only begin once you burn the boats behind you —
// the crossing with no return.
---
<svg width="560" height="180" viewBox="0 0 560 180" role="img" aria-labelledby="bb-t">
  <title id="bb-t">On the near shore, small boats are set alight and sinking — the way back deliberately closed. An arrow of no-return crosses the water to a far shore, where a figure steps forward with nothing behind her but open sea.</title>
  <!-- the burning boats on the near shore -->
  <path class="ink hair" d="M40 118 C 80 124, 120 120, 140 120" opacity="0.6" />
  <path class="ink block" d="M56 108 C 66 108, 84 108, 92 108 C 88 118, 80 122, 70 122 C 60 122, 54 116, 56 108 Z" opacity="0.7" />
  <path class="ink hair" d="M72 106 C 68 96, 76 92, 74 84 M80 106 C 84 98, 78 92, 82 86" stroke="var(--poppy)" opacity="0.7" />
  <text class="hand-label" x="44" y="146" font-size="13" opacity="0.7">the boats, burned</text>
  <!-- the crossing, no return -->
  <path class="ink spine" d="M150 96 C 240 92, 340 100, 430 96" stroke="var(--poppy)" />
  <path class="ink hair" d="M414 88 C 422 93, 428 96, 434 98 C 428 101, 421 106, 417 112" stroke="var(--poppy)" />
  <text class="hand-label hand-label--accent" x="230" y="82" font-size="13">no return</text>
  <!-- the far shore, stepping forward -->
  <path class="ink hair" d="M470 118 C 500 122, 528 120, 540 120" opacity="0.6" />
  <circle class="ink block" cx="500" cy="72" r="8" />
  <path class="ink spine" d="M500 80 C 497 96, 500 112, 498 122" />
  <path class="ink block" d="M500 92 C 512 88, 522 92, 530 96" />
  <text class="hand-label" x="474" y="146" font-size="13">step forward</text>
</svg>
